<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Jinheim</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Kilt-Wearing Freak!<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Apr 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Cut and pasted from my guild message boards a few months ago.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><i>Originally posted by Jinheim </i><br />
<b>Here's what I have found so far:<br />
<br />
Akheva:  In the second big room, between IV and Va'Dyn, there is a hall to the left with a bunch of stones in there.  Facing the big statue, I set up in the back left corner.  There is a centi there.  Kill it.  Spawn time seems to be 22 minutes.  I pulled 5 stones and killed them.  As I was about to pull more I stepped on the pile of broken white tiles near my camp, and triggered a trap.  A rock thing appeared and attacked me.  I killed it and he dropped a shard.  Total time:  25 minutes.<br />
<br />
Sanctus Seru.  Take the teleporter to the second floor.  There are plains "legionnares of the hand" and a lot of names, like "Legionnare Fircka".  About my 15th kill, a named legionnare dropped a shard.  Total time:  1 hour.  (There was someone from WC here killing them as well.  About two hours after I left, he sent me a tell asking how my luck was with shards.  He told me he'd killed about 70 with no drops yet, so your results may very)<br />
<br />
Acrylia:  A short ways from the entrance, there is a sliding white grill gate with two grimling skullcrackers in front of it.  These are supposedly the only ones that can drop shards.  I killed them both and the second one dropped a shard.  Total time: 5 minutes<br />
<br />
The Grey:  Sun Revenants around the pool in the back corner of the zone.  As my 7th kill was running away it aggroed another.  I killed the add and when i checked the two corpses they both had shards.  Total time:  30 minutes  (The guy that had the camp before me got his shard in his first quad kite, so seems to be very common).<br />
<br />
Scarlet Desert:  I was passing through and someone shouted that a shard was rotting on the sun revenants up on the plateu.  He said it was his 4th shard in 15 minutes.<br />
<br />
DSP:  I was powerleveling and alt in the hopper caves.  I was set up down in the big room at the bottom of the cave where 3 other rooms branch off.  I got about 4 shards in 2 hours.<br />
<br />
I did all of this easily solo, so it should be very easy for anyone in a duo.  Hope these details help.  Good luck. </b><hr size="1" /></blockquote>So, these are the easily soloable shards:<br />
<br />
Seru, DSP, SD, Grey, Akheva, Acrylia<br />
<br />
Maiden's Eye is also soloable pretty easily, but the camp is really really boring and you'll probably want company.  Fungus Grove is soloable too, but not really worth it.  Would be faster to get a partner.  The Deep shard is probably soloable but I didn't try.  You'll have to deal with lots of light blue adds.  Ditto Ssra shard.  Probably better for you to get a group for these last 4.<br />
<br />
edit:  where I said "really really boring" I meant "a godawful crime against humanity", sorry.</p>
	
	
	
