<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>mormegil</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Aug 2000<br />
	Location: Elgin, Ill., USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>At least 9 of the 10 are soloable. Maybe All 10.<br />
<br />
Shards:<br />
<br />
FG: Bug warriors and Royal Guards. Set up in the hall in front of the 5 spawns with priests and warriors. Kill the pat. Then kill the 5. They can be single pulled if you're good. Royals cannot be and there's always 2. Everything runs so root.<br />
<br />
AC: Kill the two PHs flanking the iron gates to the AC city area. Make a right and take the second left from the zonein (I think). Invis works fine. Runed Grimlings are fullly RM. All runs, so clear the 3-4 mobs first, as they run to them.<br />
 <br />
AR: Set up in Vadyn kill area (that nook left of the hall to his room) and pull everything, especially shaded stones and shaded golems. I've seen the rarer shaded golems drop them most. Rubble rousers also drop shards.<br />
<br />
Sanctus Seru: Just kill the 2 Legos of the Hand or their PHs at the zone-in. Everyone talks about the second floor, but I found too many pats to be decent. Stuff runs so keep root up. There's one pat behind the 2 zone guards to worry about; kill it imo.<br />
<br />
The Grey: 6-7 Sun Revenants around the pool. Single pullable. Easy.<br />
<br />
SD: Sun Revs on the plateau. Easy.<br />
<br />
SSRA: Shard drops in the mines on the lower floor. Mobs with corpse and drudge in their name drop em. NOT single-pullable, but slowable. This might be a hard solo if you have to clear. There are no pats to worry about at least.<br />
<br />
DSP: Kill sambatas and rockhoppers in the cave. Easy.<br />
<br />
Deep: Though Leeches drop em, most commonly across the invisible bridge. If you want to solo them, get buffs and/or a DA idol. Zerg to chasm (right, right, left, left, right I think) and jump. Hit /q in mid-air. Log back in. Fall a bit. Climb up back wall and move to THO tunnel left of burrower tunnel. There are 3 TH's you can single-pull. Very soloable for a 65 shaman. They can nuke, charm etc depending on what mob you get. If want to kill more than 3, the next pull brings 2.<br />
<br />
ME: Three camps.<br />
<br />
Seer (near DSP zone, 3 scouts near a rock). Suckbutt camp. Adds a many. Not worth the trouble to solo since you cannot single them without lull/harmony.<br />
<br />
Battlemaster (near AR zone, 2 scouts near a rock). Passable camp. Easy solo, just root pull. You will get adds and you will get trained.<br />
<br />
The Prophet (east of BM camp, 3 scouts, 2 near a tree). Best shard camp. Easy solo for a 65 shaman, tho the Prophet himself hit in the 170s with 1200 AC, nukes, snares and gates (bad if the other scout repops). Slowable tho. I'm told only the 2 scouts near the tree are Prophet PHs, which mirrors what I have seen, but kill the third so he doesn't add ever. Set up camp high on the hill tho and runners will start to walk to BM camp.<br />
<br />
---<br />
<br />
Other VT key bits:<br />
<br />
Staff frame: Buff and sow. Run in and spring every trap between the zone-in and IV. Zone out fast. Invis up and move to the IV hall. Instead of making a right to the IV room, make a left like you're heading to Shei. There, you'll see a portculis (iron gate), directly across from VT room. Go thru, move along wall and into a raised stone area at the center of the room. Go to the very back of the raised area, so you're facing out. There will be 5-6 sacrificed remains there. Finish the job. A shimmering presence will spawn. Hand in a wisp stone (mage summoned) and then an EE to the next mob that pops.<br />
<br />
Planar rift: Kill emp. Kill wraiths. 40 drop each time.<br />
<br />
Orb of Luclinite: Kill any SoL boss.</p>
	
	
	
